article.headline: Lipscomb 59, Gardner-Webb 57
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Brian Fisk scored 18 points and grabbed five rebounds to help Lipscomb beat Gardner-Webb 59-57 on Saturday. The Bisons (17-10, 11-5 Atlantic Sun Conference) were ahead of the Bulldogs 28-26 at the end of the first half and led by as much as 8 points in the early part of the second half. Gardner Webb's largest lead was by 5 in the first half at 6:28. Gardner-Webb (10-18, 8-9) scored 12 points in the paint while Lipscomb grabbed 24. The score was tied 4 times and the lead changed 9 times. Eddie Ard scored a total of 12 points and made four rebounds for Lipscomb. Ricky McPhee was the lead scorer with 14 points for Gardner-Webb. Chris Gash earned 11 points and grabbed 8 rebounds while Takayo Siddle contributed 10 points for the Bulldogs.
